genresAdvancedInfo.name: sound effects
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Sound effects refer to artificially created sounds that are used in various forms of media such as films, video games, and television shows. These sounds are created to enhance the overall experience for the audience and can range from simple sounds like footsteps to complex sounds like explosions or animal noises. Sound effects are often used to create a sense of realism or to add an emotional impact to a scene.
